<output>
<analysis>
<has-cmf>False. There is no CMF number present in the provided post information.</has-cmf>
<refers-to-candidate>False. The post does not refer to any specific parliamentary candidate or party.  The hashtags #Botoșani and #voceabotosani are geographical and related to the publication, not to any candidate.</refers-to-candidate>
<addresses-the-wide-population>True. The post, being a paid advertisement on Facebook, is inherently designed to reach a wide audience. The images depict a general view of Botoșani, further suggesting a broad appeal.</addresses-the-wide-population>
<electoral-objective>False. The objective of the post appears to be showcasing scenic images of Botoșani. There is no explicit or implicit attempt to influence voters' choices in the parliamentary elections.</electoral-objective>
<journalism>True. The post can be considered a form of visual journalism, presenting a photographic depiction of the city. It does not contain any commentary or opinion that could be construed as influencing the vote.</journalism>
<personal_opinion>Not applicable. The post does not express any personal opinions.</personal_opinion>
</analysis>

<conclusion>
<post_id>8970668732972302</post_id>
<electoral-propaganda-analysis>
The Facebook post is a series of photographs depicting Botoșani city in fog. The hashtags used are geographical and related to the publication's name.  There is no mention of any political party, candidate, or any call to action related to voting. The post's primary purpose seems to be to showcase the beauty of the city, not to influence the parliamentary elections. While the post falls under the "POLITICAL" category due to the publisher's nature, the content itself lacks any elements that constitute electoral propaganda as defined by Article 36 (7) of LEGE nr. 334 din 17 iulie 2006 and Article 98 t) of LEGE nr. 208 din 20 iulie 2015.
</electoral-propaganda-analysis>
<electoral-propaganda-decision>FALSE</electoral-propaganda-decision>
